      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be traceable to measured or published values with documented uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input variability to the QoI.",
      "rationale": "Model inputs including blood viscosity, density, hematocrit, pump rotational speed, and inlet flow rate were characterized with uncertainty bounds derived from device specifications and clinical literature. A comprehensive Monte Carlo analysis propagated these uncertainties through the CFD model across 500 Latin hypercube samples, yielding a 95th-percentile NIH prediction interval. All input uncertainty bounds are documented and traceable."
    },
